description: The unprecedented 30-day travel ban will bar foreign travellers, with some exceptions.
title: Coronavirus: European Union seals borders to most outsiders
title_page: Coronavirus: European Union seals borders to most outsiders - BBC News
maintext: Ireland could have 15,000 cases of coronavirus before the end of March, said PM Leo Varadkar. In a St Patrick's Day address, he warned of "significant and lasting" economic damage, and said the emergency could last into the summer. The government has already closed pubs, schools and universities.
